article.description: Kahla Roudebush scored 17 points and Cincinnati used a late run for a 65-55 victory over Xavier (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today, No. 23 AP) on Sunday.
article.headline: Cincinnati pulls away from No. 21 Xavier with 17-4 run in last three minutes
article.linkText: Cincinnati's late-game run upsets No. 21 Xavier
article.story:
CINCINNATI -- Kahla Roudebush scored 17 points and Cincinnati used a late run for a 65-55 victory over Xavier (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today, No. 23 AP) on Sunday.

Freshman Shanasa Sanders scored twice and Angel Morgan hit a 3 for her only points to key a 17-4 run over the last three minutes for Cincinnati (6-2). Sanders finished with 14 points.

April Phillips scored 16 points to lead four players in double figures for Xavier (7-3).

Until the Bearcats' late spurt, neither team in the crosstown rivalry led by more than four points. Cincinnati won for the second straight time to lead the series 22-9.

Shooting and rebounding were nearly identical with Xavier shooting 40 percent to Cincinnati's 41 percent. The Bearcats outrebounded Xavier 34-31.

The teams played an even first half with Xavier clinging to a 24-23 advantage at the break.
